---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTABand from '@/components/CTABand.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Charitable Giving Strategies | Heidi Blondin Financial"
  description="Make your generosity go further with tax-efficient charitable giving strategies. Gifts of securities, donor-advised funds, and estate giving — Heidi Blondin Financial."
>

  <section class="bg-brand-plum py-20">
    <div class="container-content max-w-3xl">
      <p class="eyebrow-light mb-5">Planning</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-display text-white text-balance" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">Charitable Giving</h1>
      <p class="font-sans text-[18px] text-white/65 mt-5 leading-relaxed">
        Giving back is part of how many Ontarians define a life well lived. Done thoughtfully, your generosity can go significantly further — for the causes you care about and for your estate.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white section-gap">
    <div class="container-content max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-brand-plum mb-6" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">Give smarter, not just more</h2>
      <div class="font-sans text-[17px] text-brand-ink/75 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>Most charitable giving in Canada happens through cash donations — which is a perfectly fine way to give. But there are strategies that dramatically increase the impact of your gift relative to its cost to you, by incorporating tax planning into your generosity.</p>
        <p>We help clients who care about legacy and community integrate charitable giving into their overall financial plan — not as an afterthought, but as a deliberate strategy.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 space-y-5">
        <div class="bg-brand-tintSage p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">Gifts of publicly traded securities</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">When you donate appreciated securities (stocks, mutual funds) directly to a registered charity, you eliminate the capital gains tax that would otherwise apply on the sale — and still receive the full charitable tax receipt. This can make your gift worth 20–30% more than a cash donation of the same size.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-brand-tintSage p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">Life insurance as a charitable gift</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">Naming a charity as the beneficiary of a life insurance policy can create a significant gift for a fraction of its face value in premiums. If the charity is made the owner of the policy, the premiums may be tax-deductible. This is a powerful tool for those who want to leave a major gift without reducing their estate significantly during their lifetime.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-brand-tintSage p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">Charitable giving through your estate</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">A bequest in your will, or naming a charity as a beneficiary of a registered account or insurance policy, can significantly reduce the tax burden on your estate. Charitable donations in the year of death and the preceding year can offset up to 100% of net income — rather than the usual 75% annual limit.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-brand-tintSage p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">Donor-advised funds</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">A donor-advised fund lets you make a lump-sum charitable contribution now (and receive the tax receipt now) while distributing the funds to specific charities over time. Useful when you want to maximize a deduction in a high-income year while retaining flexibility over which organizations benefit.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-brand-plum mb-4" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">Integrating giving into your financial plan</h2>
        <p class="font-sans text-[17px] text-brand-ink/75 leading-relaxed">
          Charitable giving strategies work best when they're part of your broader financial and estate plan — not a last-minute addition. We work with clients and their legal advisors to build giving strategies that reflect their values, their family's needs, and their tax situation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 bg-brand-tintPlum p-5 border-l-2 border-brand-plum/30">
        <p class="font-sans text-xs text-brand-ink/55 leading-relaxed">This article is for general information purposes only and does not constitute personalized financial, legal, or tax advice. Charitable giving strategies involve tax implications specific to your situation. Please consult a qualified advisor and, where appropriate, an estate lawyer before implementing any charitable giving strategy.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABand heading="Make generosity part of your plan" sub="Book a free consultation and we'll help you give in a way that makes a bigger difference." />

</BaseLayout>
